THE third annual national Mmino Wa Clap n Tap Awards are around the corner!Clap n tap gospel music has been uplifting people&rsquo;s spirits for many years. In the &rsquo;70s, community choirs such as Barorisi Ba Morena, Jerusalema Encha and Majela were popular. Now people enjoy choirs like Lejwe La Motheo, General Gospel and Mangeloi A Kgotso.&ldquo;The awards we launched in June 2014 will be held again this year at Emperors Palace, Ekurhuleni on Saturday,&rdquo; said co-founder Tebogo Mashego (32).He said after many years, their industry is starting to receive the support and recognition they always wished for.Tebogo and co-founder Stephen Mathosa (54) from Vosloorus, Ekurhuleni said this year, the awards honour OR Tambo and the youth of 1976.He said they want to commemorate the country&rsquo;s history and remind youth to strive for what they believe in, just as the youths of 1976 did.&ldquo;We will feature 1976 student activist Pauline Buyeye as key speaker,&rdquo; said Tebogo. Miss Ekurhuleni, Nontokozo Fakude, is also expected to attend.